Cover potatoes with cold water; refrigerate overnight. In a large kettle, melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and cream. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Drain potatoes; place in eight 3-qt. baking pans. Add onions. Pour the sauce over and stir gently. Cover and bake at 300 degrees F for 2 hours and 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.